               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-876" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-876" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-876" type="surname" value="BAKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-876" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BAKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to druggist, in Great Russell-street. On the 17th of July I left my hat in the corner of the kitchen, and missed it on Tuesday—the prisoner's mother lodged in the house, and he lives with her.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-877" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-877" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-877" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-877" type="given" value="FREDERICK JOHN"></interp>FREDERICK JOHN JOHNSON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable F</hi> 50.) On the 20th of July I took the prisoner into custody—I said, "Where is the hat pawned?"—he said, "Over the water, and here is the duplicate of it," giving it to me out of his stocking—he said he had been driven to it by distress—that he was turned out of his mother's house, and she would not give him any thing to eat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
